//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_trigger_build}

NOTE: This operation dispatches a container build via the vessel's
{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
using the committed
{rbtgr_build_json}
in its
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}.
All substitution values are baked at inscribe time â€” zero custom overrides at dispatch.

NOTE: This operation supports concurrent execution per the Concurrent Session Safety invariant.
Each invocation dispatches an independent trigger execution with a unique `BUILD_ID`.
Concurrent builds of the same vessel produce independent images with different
{rbtga_consecration}
timestamps.

The
{rbtr_director}
dispatches a trigger-based remote container build:

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`Â«INPUT_VESSEL_DIRÂ»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
`Â«INPUT_VESSEL_DIRÂ»` is an existing directory
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«VESSEL_ENV_FILEÂ»` as `Â«INPUT_VESSEL_DIRÂ»/rbrv.env`
.. {rbbc_require}
`Â«VESSEL_ENV_FILEÂ»` exists
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel configuration not found"

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source `Â«VESSEL_ENV_FILEÂ»` into current environment
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_sigil} defined and non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«VESSEL_SIGILÂ»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. Validate vessel directory name matches `Â«VESSEL_SIGILÂ»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if mismatch: "Vessel sigil does not match directory name"

//axhos_step
. *Validate Conjuring Configuration*:
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} defined
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext} defined
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel not configured for conjuring"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«DIRECTOR_TOKENÂ»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Trigger Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«TRIGGER_NAMEÂ»` from `RBGC_RUBRIC_TRIGGER_PREFIX` + `Â«VESSEL_SIGILÂ»`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/list[cloudbuild.triggers.list] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... filter matching `Â«TRIGGER_NAMEÂ»`
.. {rbbc_require}
exactly one trigger matches
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«TRIGGER_IDÂ»` from matching trigger resource
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not found: "Vessel trigger not found â€” run {rbtgo_rubric_inscribe} first"

//axhos_step
. *Dispatch Build via Trigger*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«RUBRIC_COMMITÂ»` as HEAD of
{rbtgr_rubric_repo}
(recorded by most recent
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe})
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/run[cloudbuild.triggers.run] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... triggerId: `Â«TRIGGER_IDÂ»`
... source.repoSource.commitSha: `Â«RUBRIC_COMMITÂ»`
.. Zero custom substitution overrides â€” all `_RBGY_*` values baked in
{rbtgr_build_json}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«BUILD_IDÂ»` from response `.metadata.build.id`
.. {rbbc_show}
build dispatched with `Â«BUILD_IDÂ»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Cloud Console URL for build monitoring

//axhos_step
. *Cloud Build Execution*:
.. NOTE: Build executes via OCI Layout Bridge pattern to solve BuildKit credential isolation. See Trade Study RBSOB for design rationale.
.. {gcb_service}
executes the following phases within the
{rbtgi_depot_project}:
... *Build Phase*: Multi-platform container compilation produces OCI Image Layout artifact in shared workspace. No registry credentials required.
... *Push Phase*: OCI artifact copied to
{rbtgi_repository}
using
{oauth_token}
obtained from
{gcb_service}
metadata server.
... *Analysis Phase*: Container image analyzed to produce SBOM (Software Bill of Materials).
... *Metadata Phase*: Build provenance, SBOM, and transcript assembled into
{rbtgi_metadata}
and stored in
{rbtgi_repository}.
.. All phases execute as
{rbtr_mason}
within the depot infrastructure.

//axhos_step
. *Wait for Build Completion*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/get[cloudbuild.builds.get] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... buildId: `Â«BUILD_IDÂ»`
.. Poll every 5 seconds for up to 20 minutes (240 attempts)
.. {rbbc_store}
`Â«BUILD_STATUSÂ»` from response `.status`
.. Continue polling while `Â«BUILD_STATUSÂ»` in [`PENDING`, `QUEUED`, `WORKING`]
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "Build timeout after 20 minutes"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if final status is not `SUCCESS`: "Build failed with status: Â«BUILD_STATUSÂ»"

//axhoo_output_of_type
{rbtga_consecration}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
build completed successfully
.. {rbbc_show}
{rbtga_consecration}
tag (dual-timestamp: inscribe + build)
.. {rbbc_show}
image available in
{rbtgi_repository}

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution builds container image and stores it in the repository.
{rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed SLSA v1.0 attestation on the built image.

==== Substitution Variable Inventory

All `_RBGY_*` substitution variables are baked into
{rbtgr_build_json}
at inscribe time by
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}.
Cloud Build resolves these from the committed JSON â€” no values are overridden at dispatch.

*Vessel identity*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_MONIKER` | Vessel sigil. Source: {rbrv_sigil}.
| `_RBGY_DOCKERFILE` | Dockerfile path relative to build context. Source: {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}.
| `_RBGY_PLATFORMS` | Target platforms. Source: {rbrv_conjure_platforms}.
|===

*Registry coordinates*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GAR_LOCATION` | Artifact Registry region. Source: {rbrr_gcp_region}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_PROJECT` | Depot project ID. Source: {rbrr_depot_project_id}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_REPOSITORY` | GAR repository name. Source: {rbrr_gar_repository}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_HOST_SUFFIX` | GAR Docker host suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_ARK_SUFFIX_IMAGE` | Image artifact tag suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_ARK_SUFFIX_ABOUT` | Metadata artifact tag suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_CRANE_TAR_GZ` | Crane release tarball URL. Source: RBGC constant.
|===

*Provenance*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GIT_COMMIT` | Main repo HEAD SHA. Placeholder in committed copy; filled at inscribe time in {rbtgr_rubric_repo} clone.
| `_RBGY_GIT_BRANCH` | Main repo branch at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_GIT_REPO` | Main repo identifier (owner/repo).
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_REPO` | {rbtgr_rubric_repo} URL. Placeholder in committed copy; filled at inscribe time in {rbtgr_rubric_repo} clone.
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_COMMIT` | {rbtgr_rubric_repo} HEAD SHA after push. Placeholder in committed copy; filled at inscribe time in {rbtgr_rubric_repo} clone.
| `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP` | Inscribe timestamp (`iYYYYMMDD_HHMMSS`). Placeholder in committed copy; filled at inscribe time in {rbtgr_rubric_repo} clone. Used by rbgjb01 to construct {rbtga_consecration}.
|===

Builder image references (step `name:` fields) are resolved to digest-pinned URIs from regime pins at inscribe time.
These are inlined directly into JSON â€” not expressed as substitution variables.

==== Script Inlining

Step scripts (`rbgjb/*.sh`) are the source of truth for build logic.
At inscribe time,
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
reads each script and inlines its content into the corresponding JSON `args` array.

Developers edit `rbgjb/*.sh` in the main repo, then run
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
to regenerate
{rbtgr_build_json}
with the updated content.
The committed JSON in the main repo is the reviewed artifact;
the {rbtgr_rubric_repo} copy is synced by inscribe.

==== Tag Construction

Each build produces a
{rbtga_consecration}
with dual timestamps:

`iÂ«INSCRIBEÂ»-bÂ«BUILDÂ»`

* `iÂ«YYYYMMDD_HHMMSSÂ»` â€” inscribe timestamp, baked as `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP`
* `bÂ«YYYYMMDD_HHMMSSÂ»` â€” build timestamp, derived at build time by `rbgjb01-derive-tag-base.sh`

Example: `i20260224_153022-b20260224_160530`

Step `rbgjb01` constructs: `TAG_BASE="${_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP}-b$(date -u +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)"`

Complete artifact tags combine vessel moniker with consecration:

* {rbtga_ark_image}: `Â«MONIKERÂ»:Â«TAG_BASEÂ»Â«ARK_SUFFIX_IMAGEÂ»`
* {rbtga_ark_about}: `Â«MONIKERÂ»:Â«TAG_BASEÂ»Â«ARK_SUFFIX_ABOUTÂ»`

Multiple builds of the same inscribed JSON sort together by inscribe prefix,
each distinguished by its build timestamp.

